0,1,&lt;p&gt;It is not an IPOHere is why that is important&lt;p&gt;,&lt;p&gt;There is a lot of debate as to whether or not the price will pop when the market opens.&lt;p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Tech listings get a lot of attention, as even those not trying to invest find the initial trade movements compelling entertainment.The initial price movement will not just represent money being made or lost, but it also could shape the digital asset industry narrative for some time to come.&lt;p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A direct listing is a relatively new option for companies wishing to go public, and one that is suited to acryptocurrencies company.The differences between direct listings and IPOs are material and are causing some confusion in the market, so in the interests of clarifying what the direct listing choice means for Coinbase, here we look at the main differences and how they may affect the initial price movement as well as the company.Investment bankers get paid a percentage of the total amount raised when they set the share price as high as they think the market will bear.&lt;p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The market on the initial trading day influences the starting price in a direct listing.There is a 10-minute period on the day of initial trading in which interested buyers and sellers can enter their offers.This information is used to calculate the current reference price.&lt;p&gt;&lt;p&gt;If it decides yes, the applicable orders that have been entered will be executed at that price.&lt;p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The direct listing will not fill the coffers with cash, but it will make it easier for the company to raise capital in the future.&lt;p&gt;&lt;p&gt;IPOs are less volatile in initial trading than direct listings due to three reasons.&lt;p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Direct listings do away with the promotional costs and much of the consulting fees.&lt;p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The cost of an IPO is one of the reasons why companies stay private.A direct listing is a better option for a company that wants to focus more on expansion than on initial share prices.The market sets the initial price rather than a group of investment bankers, which is in line with the open-access and transparent ethos of the project.&lt;p&gt;
